title: Bilal Ally rushes for 229 yards as Clay tops Baker County, stays unbeaten in district
text:
Bilal Ally rushes for 229 yards as Clay tops Baker County, stays unbeaten in district 
Sat, Oct 24, 2015 @ 3:04 am 
5-5A 
CLAY 35 
BAKER COUNTY 6 
Star of the game: Another monster night for Bilal Ally gave Clay another big win. Ally carried times for 229 yards and three touchdowns as the host Blue Devils stayed unbeaten in district play. 
Turning point: Ahead 8-6 in the second quarter, Colin Wilson ran for a TD and two-point conversion to expand the lead for the Blue Devils (5-3, 4-0). On the next drive, linebacker Jeremy Beaulieu broke on a screen and made a diving interception. Ally punched in a TD four plays later. 
On defense: Dakari Augustin and Wilson also had interceptions for Clay. ... Wilson also had a fumble recovery on defense. ... Clay held Baker County (4-4, 2-2) on fourth down five times, twice in the red zone. 
Fast facts: Down 8-0 in the first quarter, Wildcats quarterback Owen Register hit Wesley Belford on a wide receiver screen. Belford maneuvered through the defense for a 55-yard score. ... With the win, Clay will play Palatka for the district title at home next week. 
They said it: “Our offensive line did a great job opening holes and making lanes for Bilal all night. With the best back in Northeast Florida, it’s no secret we’re going to run the ball over and over and we couldn’t do it without those guys up front.” — Clay coach Josh Hoekstra George Wahl The Times-Union
